name: src/by.js
by
description:
Yields elements of the input iterable by grouping them into tuples of a
given size.

params.name: n
params.description: The size of the yielded tuples.

name: src/group.js
group
description:
Yields elements of the input iterable by grouping them into tuples
consecutive elements from the same equivalence class.
examples:
// A B C D A B
list( map( ( [ k , g ] ) => k , group( x => x , 'AAAABBBCCDAABBB' ) ) )

// AAAA BBB CC D
list( map( ( [ k , g ] ) => list( g ) , group( x => x , 'AAAABBBCCD' ) ) )

params.name: key
params.description:
The function used to determine the equivalence class
of an element.

name: src/groupby.js

content:
:people_holding_hands: [@iterable-iterator/group](https://iterable-iterator.github.io/group)
==

Iterable items grouping for JavaScript.
See [docs](https://iterable-iterator.github.io/group/index.html).

> :warning: Depending on your environment, the code may require
> `regeneratorRuntime` to be defined, for instance by importing
> [regenerator-runtime/runtime](https://www.npmjs.com/package/regenerator-runtime).

```js
import {group} from '@iterable-iterator/group';
import {identity} from '@functional-abstraction/operator';
group( identity , "AAAABBBCCAABB" ) ; // [ A AAAA ] [ B BBB ] [ C CC ] [ A AA ] [ B BB ]
```

content:
# Installation

Can be managed using
[yarn](https://yarnpkg.com/en/docs),
[npm](https://docs.npmjs.com),
or [jspm](https://jspm.org/docs).


### yarn
```terminal
yarn add @iterable-iterator/group
```

### npm
```terminal
npm install @iterable-iterator/group --save
```

### jspm
```terminal
jspm install npm:@iterable-iterator/group
```
